## Pavé Band & Hidden Halo ($2,325–$2,505)

The pavé and hidden halo category in platinum is the most review-concentrated section in this guide. The Pavé Knife Edge Lotus Basket alone carries 251 reviews. Pavé bands in platinum benefit from work-hardening at the bead-set prong points that hold each pavé diamond — the pavé beads resist spreading over time in platinum where they would gradually loosen in gold.

[![Pavé Knife Edge Lotus Basket Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum by James Allen — princess cut center diamond in knife-edge lotus basket setting with pavé band in platinum, 251 reviews on Blue Nile](/images/princess-cut-platinum-pave-lotus-setting.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pave-knife-edge-lotus-basket-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315129?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational "Pavé Knife Edge Lotus Basket Platinum (JA) — $2,340 on Blue Nile")

**[Plain Shank Floating Halo Engagement Ring in Platinum — $2,325](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/plain-shank-floating-halo-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-203752?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
58 reviews. A floating halo sits above a plain (unadorned) shank — the pavé halo ring appears to float above the band because the connection between band and halo is minimized. The plain shank contrasts with the intricate floating halo: all visual complexity is concentrated at the center stone. With G-VS1 = **$4,861 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,537 total**.

**[Pavé Knife Edge Lotus Basket Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum (JA) — $2,340](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pave-knife-edge-lotus-basket-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315129?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
251 reviews. The most-reviewed setting in this section. Knife-edge shank with a lotus basket beneath the center stone — the basket structure is shaped like a lotus flower with petal-like platinum forms holding the diamond from below. Pavé diamonds along the knife-edge shank add sparkle along the band profile. In platinum, both the knife-edge ridge and the lotus basket petal forms maintain their dimensional detail over decades. With G-VS1 = **$4,876 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,552 total**.

**[Cut Down Pavé Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum (JA) — $2,410](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/cut-down-pave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315163?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
40 reviews. Cut-down pavé is a specific pavé technique where the metal around each pavé diamond is cut away from the sides, reducing the visible metal between diamonds to a minimum. This maximizes diamond exposure per unit of band area — the cut-down technique creates a denser-looking diamond surface than standard bead-set pavé. With G-VS1 = **$4,946 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,622 total**.

[![Crown Pavé Hidden Halo Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum by James Allen — princess cut center diamond with hidden halo beneath crown and pavé band in platinum, 26 reviews on Blue Nile](/images/princess-cut-platinum-crown-halo-setting.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/crown-pave-hidden-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315147?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational "Crown Pavé Hidden Halo Platinum (JA) — $2,470 on Blue Nile")

**[Lace Bridge Solitaire Plus Hidden Halo Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum (1/5 ct. tw.) — $2,420](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/lace-bridge-solitaire-plus-hidden-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-5-ct-tw-item-197062?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
2 reviews. A lace bridge connects the band to the setting head — decorative platinum lace-like metalwork spanning the gap where band meets center stone mount. The hidden halo is positioned beneath the crown, visible when looking at the ring from the side or at eye level but invisible from above: the top-view silhouette reads as a solitaire while the side view reveals the halo. Setting includes 1/5 ct tw hidden halo diamonds. With G-VS1 = **$4,956 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,632 total**.

**[Petite Baguette and Pavé Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum — $2,430](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-baguette-and-pave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-148363?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
4 reviews. Petite baguette-cut side accents flanking the princess cut center, with pavé on the band. Baguette diamonds have step-cut facets — they are more color-sensitive than brilliant-cut round accents. In platinum (neutral metal, no warmth), G-color baguette accents are acceptable; the platinum environment does not amplify their natural warmth. With G-VS1 = **$4,966 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,642 total**.

**[Crown Pavé Hidden Halo Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum (JA) — $2,470](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/crown-pave-hidden-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315147?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
26 reviews. Crown pavé means the prong arms that hold the center stone have pavé diamonds set directly into them — the crown of the setting sparkles. Hidden halo beneath the crown creates a double-brightness effect: pavé-set prongs from above, halo from below. In platinum, the pavé-set prong crown does not risk loss of pavé diamonds from prong thinning over time. With G-VS1 = **$5,006 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,682 total**.

**[Delicate Ballerina Halo Diamond Engagement Ring in Platinum — $2,505](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/delicate-ballerina-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-192595?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
1 review. Ballerina halo: the halo diamonds are set at an upward angle around the center stone, tilted outward like a ballerina's tutu rather than lying flat in the plane of the center stone. This creates a tiered, dimensional halo effect with visual depth. In platinum, the angled halo prongs that hold each diamond at its tilted angle maintain their positioning through work-hardening at the setting stress points. With G-VS1 = **$5,041 total**. With G-VS2 = **$4,717 total**.

